  "prompt": "How do I find my first job?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to help you find your first job:\n\n1. Prepare your resume\n- Highlight education, skills, and any internships or volunteer work\n- Have someone review it for feedback\n\n2. Explore job search platforms\n- Indeed\n- LinkedIn\n- Glassdoor\n- ZipRecruiter\n- Local job boards\n\n3. Network\n- Ask friends and family about job opportunities\n- Connect with alumni from your school\n- Attend job fairs\n- Use LinkedIn to connect with professionals\n\n4. Check entry-level positions\n- Internships\n- Part-time jobs\n- Assistant roles\n- Trainee positions\n\n5. Leverage your school's career center\n- Get job search advice\n- Access job listings\n- Practice interview skills\n\n6. Tailor your applications\n- Customize resume and cover letter for each job\n- Highlight relevant skills\n- Show enthusiasm\n\n7. Prepare for interviews\n- Research the company\n- Practice common interview questions\n- Dress professionally\n- Follow up after the interview\n\n8. Consider alternative paths\n- Freelancing\n- Temporary work\n- Volunteer work\n- Online gig platforms\n\n9. Be persistent and patient\n- Apply to multiple positions\n- Don't get discouraged by rejections",
